===Viewing transaction history===
To view the history of your transactions, navigate to the '''Marketplace''' page on the [[Special:MyLanguage/Main Menu|Main Menu]], proceed to the '''Wallet''' section, and then choose the '''Transactions''' tab. Alternatively, you can view it on the {{VRC link|https://vrchat.com/home/marketplace/wallet |VRChat website}}. 

The Transactions tab shows the history of the user's VRChat Credits on their account. Listing the name of the product, the amount of credits, the remaining balance after the purchase, the recipient, the date of purchase, and the type of transaction.

To view your purchases or active and expired subscriptions, navigate to the '''Purchases & Subscriptions''' tab of the '''Marketplace''' page.  

The Purchases tab lists any listing you bought, including its type, date of purchase and expiration, and details. While, the Subscriptions tab includes the same details as the Purchases tab, just instead for subscriptions. It is split up by an "Active" and "Expired" dropdown, and also includes an option to renew the subscription or cancel it.

==Avatar Marketplace==
''<small>See also: [[Avatar Marketplace]] for more detailed information.</small>''

The '''Avatar Marketplace''' is a feature announced by VRChat on May 14, 2025<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MWH1RA3bEz0</ref><ref>https://ask.vrchat.com/t/announcing-the-avatar-marketplace/43554</ref>, as an expansion of the Creator Economy. This update introduces a native system for selling and buying avatars directly within VRChat using VRChat Credits.

With the [[Avatar Marketplace]], users can purchase avatars that are automatically added to their VRChat account without the need to manually upload avatars through Unity. Purchased avatars are permanently accessible to the buyer outside of extraordinary circumstances. <!-- TODO: elaborate on extraordinary circumstances, like if the avatar contains TOS or potentially illegal content -->

Avatars listed on the marketplace can be locally previewed before purchase, meaning the avatar is only visible to the user while using the try-on feature.

The Avatar Marketplace update adds three new upper tabs to the Avatars tab in the [[Main Menu]]. The '''Explore''' tab lets a user search for avatars for sale in the Marketplace, as well as varying categories of avatars for sale. The '''My Avatars''' tab utilizes the traditional avatar menu, with your uploaded avatars, favorited avatars, as well as a new section for "Purchased" avatars from the marketplace. Lastly, the '''My Current Avatar''' tab shows the avatar details of an avatar that you are currently wearing.

Users interested in [https://ask.vrchat.com/t/avatar-marketplace-faq-for-sellers/43555 selling avatars] on the Avatar Marketplace need to enroll in VRChat's Creator Economy Program for approval.

==Enrolling in the Creator Economy Program==

{{Thumb|{{YouTube|cNvmvPa4T3c|thumb=File:YTThumb_cNvmvPa4T3c_CreatorEconomy.webp|title=What's the VRChat Creator Economy?}}|}}
To be able to enroll in the Creator Economy Program, a user must have uploaded content and have access to the VRChat Creator Companion, and then [https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/vrc-econ-apply apply to become a seller], as long as they are eligible:

====Eligibility<!-- Incomplete. The CE has additional eligibility criteria, listed in the application form: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/vrc-econ-apply -->====   

*Be a User who is 18 years of age or older.
*Have a VRChat account that has been active for at least 30 days.
*Have a verified email address associated with your Account.
* Be a community member in good standing at all times while using the Platform, with no suspensions or bans from the Platform or the VRC Creator Economy in the last 90 days.
*Use the Platform in strict compliance with CE Rules, the Terms, the Community Guidelines, and the requirements set out in ''Creator Economy Program Rules Section 5''.
*Not engage in any of the following activities: scamming, phishing, false advertising, attempting to exchange Credits for real currency other than through the Platform, or any illegal or unethical activities.
*Meet any other eligibility requirements that we or our CE Partner may establish from time to time in our or their sole discretion, including but not limited to: 
**Having all applicable tax forms on file with the relevant CE Partner
**Completing any applicable CE Partner’s Know Your Customer registration, as required by such CE Partner
{{VRC link|https://hello.vrchat.com/legal/economy |See here}} to view the full Creator Economy Program Rules.

